            What is a cooling spiral conveyor?
            <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-ink-muted group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform flex-shrink-0 ml-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"></path></svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="text-ink-muted leading-relaxed space-y-3">
            <p>A cooling spiral conveyor moves baked products through a helical path inside a tower, providing extended <a href="/industries/food-conveyors/cooling/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">cooling</a> time in a small floor footprint. A single spiral replaces 200+ feet of straight-line cooling conveyor in as little as 100 square feet. Spirals can be ambient, forced-air, or refrigerated.</p>
