          <div class="text-ink-muted leading-relaxed space-y-3">
            <p>A proofing conveyor transports dough through a temperature- and humidity-controlled enclosure (80-110 F, 70-85% RH) where yeast fermentation occurs. Spiral proofers maximize floor space; straight-line proofers suit smaller operations. Dwell times range from 30 to 90 minutes depending on dough type.</p>
